main event: Two lights were observed breaking apart over Wake Island on 13 September 1962.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 1 minute and was made by civilian aviation,The lights were seen breaking into pieces,Scattered larger objects were observed in close proximity with various structural shapes,The report concludes the sighting was likely due to the decay of a satellite,The altitude at which the objects were initially observed was approximately 19 thousand feet.
sighted object: two lights breaking into pieces and larger scattered objects
